race.comment: They'll go like the clappers in this. COLOPHON (6) couldn't have been more impressive with a dominant Gold Coast win when resuming and actually drops 6kgs on that victory when you factor in the claim. Has only missed the quinella spot once in four attempts over this six-furlong journey and should be right there when the judge calls a halt. KINROSS LANE (16) has two wins and a placing from three starts over this trip and should get a soft run in transit from the favourable draw. Capable of playing a big role in the finish. BOLD COMIC (4) is an honest commodity who doesn't know how to put in a poor one. Top-three contender on recent efforts. PARETO (7) was too bad to be true last time out but the form prior was full of merit. Can bounce right back. BIG BOY GEORGE (9) is a last-start winner who looks one for the exotics players.
